-- Polsky, Founder of Invenergy, Buys Dimon's Chicago Mansion, Crain's Says
-- B y   D a n   H a r t
-- 2010-09-26T16:40:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-26/polsky-founder-of-invenergy-buys-dimon-s-chicago-mansion-crain-s-says.html
Michael Polsky , founder of closely
held Invenergy LLC, purchased the Chicago mansion owned by
JPMorgan Chase & Co. Chief Executive Officer  Jamie Dimon ,
Crain’s Chicago Business reported, citing unidentified sources.  The 13,500-square-foot (1,253-square-meter) home on Banks
Street was listed at $6.95 million, the weekly magazine said on
its website. The article didn’t say how much the mansion sold
for.  Chicago-based Invenergy develops, owns and operates
renewable and other clean-energy generation plants in North
America and Europe.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Dan Hart  in Washington at 
 dahart@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at   swier@bloomberg.net . 